# Xcode Tools MCP

`user-xcode-tools` for **any** Xcode op it covers — not just builds/tests. No `xcodebuild`, `swift test`, `simctl`, manual `pbxproj` edits, or other CLI when MCP tool exists.

## Workflow

1. Confirm `user-xcode-tools` enabled
2. Read tool schema before `CallMcpTool`
3. `XcodeListWindows` → `tabIdentifier` (most tools need it)
4. List tools in MCP folder if unsure; use match

## Tool categories

**Build & run:** `BuildProject`, `RunProject`, `StopProject`, `GetBuildLog`, `GetConsoleOutput`

**Tests:** `GetTestList`, `RunAllTests`, `RunSomeTests`

**Scheme & destination:** `XcodeListSchemes`, `XcodeSwitchScheme`, `XcodeListRunDestinations`, `XcodeSwitchRunDestination`

**Settings & flags:** `GetTargetBuildSettings`, `UpdateTargetBuildSetting`, `GetFileCompilerFlags`, `UpdateFileCompilerFlags`

**Issues & diagnostics:** `XcodeListNavigatorIssues`, `XcodeRefreshCodeIssuesInFile`, `GetTopCrashIssues`, `GetCrashIssueLogs`, `GetTopFieldPerformanceIssues`, `GetFieldPerformanceIssueLogs`

**Device interaction:** `DeviceInteractionStartSession`, `DeviceInteractionInstallAndRun`, `DeviceInteractionSynthesize`, `DeviceInteractionEndSession`

**Debug:** `InvokeDebuggerCommand`, `RunCodeSnippet`

**Project files:** `XcodeRead`, `XcodeWrite`, `XcodeUpdate`, `XcodeLS`, `XcodeGlob`, `XcodeGrep`, `XcodeMV`, `XcodeRM`, `XcodeMakeDir`, `XcodeGetCurrentFile`, `AddEntitlement`, `AddInfoPlist`

**Localization:** `StringCatalogRead`, `StringCatalogEdit`, `StringCatalogContext`, `LocalizationPlanner`

**UI:** `RenderPreview`

**Docs:** `DocumentationSearch`

## MCP unavailable

**Stop.** No silent CLI fallback.

Tell user: MCP missing or failed; Xcode may need permission prompt approved; enable MCP in Cursor or approve CLI fallback.

CLI only after explicit user OK ("use command line", "fallback to xcodebuild").

## Failures

Read `fullLogPath`, `fullSummaryPath`, or `GetBuildLog` — not truncated summary alone.
